1. *Smetam* svojim roditeljima kad hoću da gledam televiziju. (I bother my parents when I want to watch TV.)
2. *Smeta* mi kada ljudi žvaću žvaku glasno. (It bothers me when people chew gum loudly.)
3. *Ne smeta* mi da sedim ovde. (It doesn't bother me to sit here.)
4. *Smetaću* vam ako ne budete radili svoj posao. (I will bother you if you don't do your job.)
5. *Smetaju* mi buka i svetla u gradu. (Noise and lights in the city bother me.)
6. *Da li smetam* ako ostanem ovde i dalje? (Am I bothering you if I stay here?)
7. Molim vas da *ne smetate* dok govorim na telefon. (Please don't disturb me while I'm on the phone.)
8. *Smetalo* mi je kada su mi stalno zvonili na vrata. (It bothered me when someone kept ringing my doorbell.)
9. Neću ti *smeći* ako mi ne ponudiš da probam. (I won't bother you if you don't offer me to try.)
10. *Smetnja* u komunikaciji je često uzrok nesporazuma. (Disturbance in communication is often the cause of misunderstandings.)

Note: The word "smetam" can have several meanings in different contexts, including "to bother, to disturb, to hinder, to impede". The translations provided are the most appropriate in the given context.